summaries.short: In this series, Latin musicians reveal a personal secret to the "tiny" audience before them and perform songs that are meaningful to them.

summaries.short: Argentine pop singer Diego Torres is a three-time Latin Grammy(R) winner with 7 Billboard Top Ten hits.
summaries.full: Argentine pop singer Diego Torres is a three-time Latin Grammy(R) winner with 7 Billboard Top Ten hits. His second album, Tratar De Estar Mejor, went platinum five times in Argentina.

summaries.short: Mon Laferte is the Chilean singer with the highest sales in the digital era, with 1.5 million digital albums and singles sold.
summaries.full: Mon Laferte is the Chilean singer with the highest sales in the digital era, with 1.5 million digital albums and singles sold. She has won Latin Grammys(R) for Alternative Song (2017) and Alternative Music Album (2019).

summaries.short: Natalia Jimenez is the former lead singer of the Spanish pop band La Quinta Estacion.
summaries.full: Natalia Jimenez is the former lead singer of the Spanish pop band La Quinta Estacion, which won a Grammy(R) for Best Latin Pop Album in 2010. Now, Jimenez is a solo artist who has been thrice nominated for Latin Grammys(R).

summaries.short: Colombian group Piso 21 was nominated for Best New Artist at the Latin Grammy(R) Awards.
summaries.full: Colombian group Piso 21 was nominated for Best New Artist at the Latin Grammy(R) Awards and recently collaborated with will.i.am on a new single, "Mami."

summaries.short: Performers in this episode include: Sebastian Yatra, Natti Natasha, Juanes and Jackie Cruz.
summaries.full: In this episode, Sebastian Yatra, who always sleeps with socks on, performs "No Hay Nadie Mas" and "Robarte un Beso"; Natti Natasha, who doesn't know how to swim, performs "Dutti Love" and "La Mejor Version De Mi"; plus, Juanes performs "La Camisa Negra" and "Island in the Sun"; and Jackie Cruz performs "Melly 16" and covers Amy Winehouse's "Valerie."

summaries.short: Chilean singer-songwriter Cami is a pop star on her way to the top.
summaries.full: Chilean singer-songwriter Cami calls Puerto Rican singer Luis Fonsi a mentor, and with multiple Grammy(R)-winner Sebastian Krys as her producer, she is a pop star on her way to the top.

summaries.short: Costa Rican pop singer and multi-instrumentalist Debi Nova had a number one dance hit, "One Rhythm."
summaries.full: Costa Rican pop singer and multi-instrumentalist Debi Nova had a number one dance hit, "One Rhythm," before appearing on recordings with such artists as Britney Spears and Ricky Martin.

summaries.short: Draco Rosa, writer of the Ricky Martin hit "La Vida Loca," started his musical career at age 14 as a member of Menudo.
summaries.full: Draco Rosa, writer of the Ricky Martin hit "La Vida Loca," started his musical career at age 14 as a member of Menudo. The singer, songwriter, composer, multi-instrumentalist, dancer, record producer and entrepreneur won a Grammy(R) for Best Latin Pop album in 2014 and has won multiple Latin Grammys(R).

summaries.short: Musical duo Jesse y Joy are a brother-sister act from Mexico City. They have won six Latin Grammys(R).
summaries.full: Musical duo Jesse y Joy are a brother-sister act from Mexico City. They have won a Grammy(R) for Best Latin Pop Album and six Latin Grammys(R).

summaries.short: Puerto Rican-born singer-producer Tommy Torres has won three Latin Grammys(R).
summaries.full: Puerto Rican-born singer-producer Tommy Torres has won three Latin Grammys(R).

summaries.short: Actor, entrepreneur, vocalist and New Yorker of Dominican descent, Jackie Cruz rose to fame for her role on "Orange Is the New Black."
summaries.full: Actor, entrepreneur, vocalist and New Yorker of Dominican descent, Jackie Cruz rose to fame for her portrayal of "Flaca" on Orange Is the New Black. Cruz is a three-time SAG Award winner and was named on THR's "Top Latino Powerhouses under 40" list. Music was always Cruz's first love; her full-length album came out in October.

summaries.full: Sebastian Yatra grew up in Miami learning to play guitar, piano, and sing. At 19, his single "El Psicologo" became a hit in his native Colombia.

summaries.full: Alejandra Guzman is a Mexican singer-songwriter and actress with over 30 million albums sold, and winner of a Latin Grammy(R) for Best Rock Solo Album.
